results.name: Numerator of the average of the multiset of prime indices of n.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798.
example: The prime indices of 12 are {1,1,2}, with average 4/3, so a(12) = 4.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Jul 13 2019
